body:
I was skeptical of the enumerator for arrays allocating, so I ran a profile:

```csharp
    [MemoryDiagnoser]
    public class LoopAllocationTest
    {
        public static void RunProfile()
        {
            BenchmarkRunner.Run<LoopAllocationTest>();
        }

        private byte[] _nums;

        [GlobalSetup]
        public void Setup()
        {
            _nums = new byte[1000000];
            new Random().NextBytes(_nums);
        }

        [Benchmark(Baseline = true)]
        public void RunForLoop()
        {
            for (int i = 0; i < _nums.Length; i++)
            {
                int k = _nums[i];
            }
        }

        [Benchmark]
        public void RunForEachLoop()
        {
            foreach (int k in _nums)
            {
                ;
            }
        }
    }
```

Results:

```
BenchmarkDotNet=v0.12.1, OS=Windows 10.0.19041.450 (2004/?/20H1)
Intel Core i7-8700K CPU 3.70GHz (Coffee Lake), 1 CPU, 12 logical and 6 physical cores
